<subSubSection id="8A5D92614A8AB5596CAC47B806B7EC29" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="274C7BF403460DDD373ADCDF8F4494AA" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName id="73862279EFF24A25013D62C0F4D30384" authorityName="Bank" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Meijeriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Meijeriella</taxonomicName>
Bank, 1985, Heldia 1 (2): 41.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B5F165BF84FD629C40DC04C11338AEC" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName id="4528C9096BB8363DBDDE62C512D0CBAC" authorityName="Orstan &amp; Yildirim" authorityYear="2004" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Borlumastus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Borlumastus</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="39168BD4993DF745CDF87D2C9B00BD5D" originalValue="Örstan">Oerstan</normalizedToken>
&amp; Yildirim, 2004, Basteria, 68: 126.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="33F78155BA43FDF01BB08F0B523CCE5C" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" type="type species">
<paragraph id="ABA77FEBB3627933C40AD9B789946472" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD44D033B164E62ECAD77CFB8B81FB1C" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName id="B1CE28873FF7AE7F4217B20654515E47" authorityName="Bank" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Meijeriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="canaliculata">
<emphasis id="975BC117C7BECF500EED7667E9978F22" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Meijeriella canaliculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bank, 1985 (by original designation).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="313763B56F9C837C24B40B77E0F047E6" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
In their paper, 
<bibRefCitation id="29F67D6537A670D20E3798F0CC008BC1" author="Oerstan, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" refId="B16" refString="Oerstan, A, Yildirim, MZ, 2004. Borlumastus gen. Nov. (Gastropoda, Pulmonata, Enidae), a new land snail genus from Turkey. Basteria, Leiden, 68 (4/6): 125-129." title="Borlumastus gen. Nov. (Gastropoda, Pulmonata, Enidae), a new land snail genus from Turkey. Basteria, Leiden, 68 (4 / 6): 125 - 129." year="2004">
<normalizedToken id="7864E033B467E295762AEC155A9C9001" originalValue="Örstan">Oerstan</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="BF00878D087AD3542CBAF83B1541BCDA" originalValue="Yıldırım">Yildirim</normalizedToken>
(2004)
</bibRefCitation>
used the following autapomorphic characters to separate their new genus 
<taxonomicName id="F805D6CFB9130665013CC9A32C273E93" authorityName="Orstan &amp; Yildirim" authorityYear="2004" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Borlumastus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7F6B02CC4C22C3F6F41E874DC13EBB3F" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Borlumastus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: presence of a single palatal tooth, and secondly, attachment position of the penial retractor muscle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C317C2B0F7D3D6E0774E01F29676C488" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
However, presence or absence of the palatal, columellar, and parietal teeth cannot be used for characterization of genera within the family 
<taxonomicName id="79B69A614E815322054A53EAA44150E2" authorityName="B.B.Woodward" authorityYear="1903" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Pulmonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Enidae</taxonomicName>
. For example, 
<taxonomicName id="E8498A2952AE544692346F9B9FB3D873" baseAuthorityName="Mortillet" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Pseudochondrula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tetrodon">
<emphasis id="D7F38A262127CBA1F4E645E8CF97629B" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Pseudochondrula tetrodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Mortillet, 1854) displays a number of variations in its apertural dentition, there are specimens without teeth as well as specimens with up to four teeth, sometimes to be found mixed up in the same population. On the other hand, browsing the species currently affiliated to 
<taxonomicName id="F0186EB5F4C76F64FEE1D742D735B4CB" authorityName="O. Boettger" authorityYear="1883" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Euchondrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1F080434D1D8861BF86078F2BA41CF7F" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Euchondrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Boettger, 1883 it becomes clear that in this genus, species may differ in their dentition, but still are considered to belong to the same genus. Thus it is obvious that presence or absence of a single tooth does not qualify as autapomorphic character on genus-level taxa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD64FFAF53CB40AF5AB4C9D35232282E" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
The attachment position of the penial retractor muscle on the male genital system is said to differ in 
<taxonomicName id="37D7016E649BE21EF439480125A2D16F" authorityName="Orstan &amp; Yildirim" authorityYear="2004" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Borlumastus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="98B2A1576A86BEB2276E5233CE9B1BDD" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Borlumastus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from that in 
<taxonomicName id="B4B61E43A8D0C43BD0CD4A454F8606C5" authorityName="Bank" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Meijeriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A675EB98217257B421113318A00DF24C" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Meijeriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because in the latter genus, the muscle would attach at the epiphallus. Having investigated the genital anatomy of both species, 
<taxonomicName id="6C96719D8FAEC86AFF430958C8BA4070" authorityName="Bank" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Meijeriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="canaliculata">
<emphasis id="DEB670E60043C936F4C8CFED3596FC47" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Meijeriella canaliculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="131EC5DD18B8D70055155370910A5D81" baseAuthorityName="L. Pfeiffer" baseAuthorityYear="1847" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Meijeriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="frivaldskyi">
<emphasis id="D75D977209684D9A99C53878522133F0" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Meijeriella frivaldskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Turkey it can be said that the muscles embraces the distal end of the epiphallus including a small area of the terminal part of the proximal penis section. This makes clear that there is virtually no difference in the attachment position of this muscle in all three species. For these reasons we see no argument left to keep the genus 
<taxonomicName id="40C943672BC6266ABF567DC27122BF08" authorityName="Orstan &amp; Yildirim" authorityYear="2004" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Borlumastus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3B19253FEFB66E7CA8A1B02C0AD3D25F" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Borlumastus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and relegate it into the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="26BD3B5E74CBE731F9EAF8F5565FC14D" authorityName="Bank" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Meijeriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AB06066B6E3716A78052B08691CDD835" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Meijeriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bank, 1985.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A6E271AA741E4F62D5E778DF735522C4" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
Remark: It has been argued that the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="24C25FF175DE260EE80570AAA6585ACA" authorityName="Bank" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Meijeriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="159A631CF43C31CCC6052D8C89894027" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Meijeriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bank, 1985 is preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName id="C14A8C5B74687718CF2CE130115B49C3" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" genus="Meyeriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0531559B516534DF8EB8547416D135B" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Meyeriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Krausse, 1917 (Arch. Naturgesch., 82, A1: 95, in 
<taxonomicName id="640B6E055992D5DBFBF4C66D525AB01F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Hymenoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Hymenoptera</taxonomicName>
). However, genus-level names are ruled by §56.1 and §56.2 ICZN clearly stating &quot;Even if the difference between two genus-group names is only one letter, they are not homonyms&quot;. Thus, 
<taxonomicName id="BDF155DC6F70E20396D42619FB875C9E" authorityName="Bank" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Enidae" genus="Meijeriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B16E71418B8A9B3FA3BACBB764CF62C9" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Meijeriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has to be kept as a valid genus.
</paragraph>
